    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Day 4: Introduction to Neural Networks\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"<a target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"https://colab.research.google.com/github/LuWidme/uk259/blob/main/demos/06_Neural_Networks.ipynb\\\">\\n\",\n",
    "    \"  <img src=\\\"https://colab.research.google.com/assets/colab-badge.svg\\\" alt=\\\"Open In Colab\\\"/>\\n\",\n",
    "    \"</a>\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Duration:** 2-3 hours  \\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Prerequisites:** Python basics, NumPy, understanding of classification  \\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Learning Objectives:**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Understand what neural networks are and how they work\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Learn the key components: layers, activation functions, loss functions\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Build your first neural network with TensorFlow/Keras\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Train a model to recognize handwritten digits\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Evaluate model performance and make predictions\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Apply neural networks to image classification tasks\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Datasets Used:** MNIST (handwritten digits), Fashion MNIST (clothing items)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"---\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## What are Neural Networks?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Simple explanation:** Neural networks are computer programs inspired by how the human brain works. They learn to recognize patterns by looking at many examples.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Real-World Analogy\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Learning to recognize cats:**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. As a child, you see many cats\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Your brain notices patterns: fur, whiskers, pointed ears, tail\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Eventually, you can recognize a cat you've never seen before\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Neural networks learn the same way!\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### How Neural Networks Work\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Think of a neural network as layers of simple decision-makers:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"```\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Input Layer          Hidden Layers           Output Layer\\n\",\n",
    "    \"(pixels)            (pattern detectors)      (predictions)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"  ○                     ○  ○  ○                   ○\\n\",\n",
    "    \"  ○  ───────→          ○  ○  ○      ───────→     ○\\n\",\n",
    "    \"  ○                     ○  ○  ○                   ○\\n\",\n",
    "    \"  ○\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Image               \\\"Is it curved?\\\"           \\\"It's a 3!\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                    \\\"Has a loop?\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                    \\\"Has straight line?\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"```\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Each layer:**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Takes input from the previous layer\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Performs calculations (weighted sum + activation)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Passes results to the next layer\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Why Neural Networks?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Traditional programming:**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"```\\n\",\n",
    "    \"IF (has_fur AND has_whiskers AND has_tail):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    return \\\"cat\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"```\\n\",\n",
    "    \"→ Hard to write rules for complex patterns!\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Neural networks:**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"```\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Show 10,000 examples\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Network learns the pattern automatically\\n\",\n",
    "    \"```\\n\",\n",
    "    \"→ Great for images, speech, text, and complex patterns!\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Common Applications\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Image recognition**: Face unlock, medical diagnosis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Natural language**: Chatbots, translation, text generation\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Recommendation**: Netflix, Spotify, YouTube\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Game playing**: Chess, Go, video games\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Autonomous vehicles**: Self-driving cars\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"---\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Setup\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We'll use **TensorFlow** with **Keras** (a high-level API that makes building neural networks easy).\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
