    "   ],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": 3\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Preprocess the Data\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Important step:** Neural networks work best when input values are small (0-1 range).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Current:** Pixels are 0-255  \\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Goal:** Normalize to 0-1 by dividing by 255\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2026-01-13T13:26:54.636728100Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2026-01-13T13:26:54.446091500Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Normalize pixel values to [0, 1] range\\n\",\n",
    "    \"x_train = x_train / 255.0\\n\",\n",
    "    \"x_test = x_test / 255.0\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"After normalization:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"  Min value: {x_train.min()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"  Max value: {x_train.max()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"  Mean value: {x_train.mean():.3f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\n✓ Data preprocessed and ready for training!\\\")\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [\n",
    "    {\n",
    "     \"name\": \"stdout\",\n",
    "     \"output_type\": \"stream\",\n",
    "     \"text\": [\n",
    "      \"After normalization:\\n\",\n",
    "      \"  Min value: 0.0\\n\",\n",
    "      \"  Max value: 1.0\\n\",\n",
    "      \"  Mean value: 0.131\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\n\",\n",
    "      \"✓ Data preprocessed and ready for training!\\n\"\n",
    "     ]\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": 4\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Part 2: Building Your First Neural Network\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Understanding the Architecture\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We'll build a simple neural network with 3 layers:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Input Layer (Flatten)**: Converts 28×28 image → 784 numbers\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Hidden Layer (Dense)**: 128 neurons that learn patterns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Output Layer (Dense)**: 10 neurons (one per digit 0-9)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"```\\n\",\n",
    "    \"28×28 image  →  Flatten  →  Dense(128)  →  Dense(10)  →  Prediction\\n\",\n",
    "    \"  (784)           (784)       (128)          (10)         (0-9)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"```\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Key Concepts\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Flatten Layer:**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Converts 2D image (28×28) into 1D array (784)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Like unrolling a grid into a long line\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Dense Layer (Fully Connected):**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Each neuron connected to ALL neurons in previous layer\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Learns complex patterns through these connections\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Activation Function (ReLU):**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- ReLU = Rectified Linear Unit\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Adds non-linearity: `ReLU(x) = max(0, x)`\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Allows network to learn complex patterns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Output Layer:**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- 10 neurons (one per digit)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Each outputs a score (logit)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Highest score = predicted digit\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2026-01-13T13:26:54.764111500Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2026-01-13T13:26:54.639247800Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Build the model\\n\",\n",
    "    \"model = keras.Sequential([\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Layer 1: Flatten the input\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    keras.layers.Flatten(input_shape=(28, 28), name='flatten'),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Layer 2: Hidden layer with 128 neurons\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu', name='hidden'),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Layer 3: Output layer with 10 neurons (one per digit)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    keras.layers.Dense(10, name='output')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Display model architecture\\n\",\n",
    "    \"model.summary()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\n📝 Model Architecture:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"  1. Flatten: 28×28 = 784 inputs\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"  2. Dense(128): Hidden layer with 128 neurons\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"  3. Dense(10): Output layer with 10 neurons (digits 0-9)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\n  Total parameters: {model.count_params():,}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"  (These are the 'weights' the network will learn!)\\\")\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [\n",
    "    {\n",
    "     \"name\": \"stderr\",\n",
    "     \"output_type\": \"stream\",\n",
    "     \"text\": [\n",
