    "   ],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": 6\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### What is Softmax?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Softmax** converts raw scores (logits) into probabilities that sum to 1:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"```\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Logits:         [-2.5, 0.3, 1.8, -0.5, ...]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                      ↓ softmax\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Probabilities:  [0.02, 0.13, 0.58, 0.05, ...]  (sum = 1.0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"```\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This makes outputs interpretable as confidence levels!\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"---\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Part 4: Compiling the Model\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Before training, we need to configure:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Optimizer**: How to adjust weights (Adam is a good default)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Loss function**: How to measure errors\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Metrics**: What to track (accuracy)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Loss Function: Sparse Categorical Crossentropy\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**What it does:** Measures how wrong the predictions are.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Low loss** = good predictions\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **High loss** = bad predictions\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Goal: Minimize loss during training\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**\\\"Sparse Categorical\\\"** means:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Categorical: Multiple classes (0-9)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Sparse: Labels are integers (not one-hot encoded)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2026-01-13T13:26:54.870098600Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2026-01-13T13:26:54.845935200Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Compile the model\\n\",\n",
    "    \"model.compile(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    optimizer='adam',  # Adaptive learning rate optimizer\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    loss=keras.losses.SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(from_logits=True),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    metrics=['accuracy']  # Track accuracy during training\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"✓ Model compiled and ready to train!\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\nConfiguration:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"  Optimizer: Adam (adaptive learning rate)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"  Loss: SparseCategoricalCrossentropy\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"  Metrics: Accuracy\\\")\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [\n",
    "    {\n",
    "     \"name\": \"stdout\",\n",
    "     \"output_type\": \"stream\",\n",
    "     \"text\": [\n",
    "      \"✓ Model compiled and ready to train!\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\n\",\n",
    "      \"Configuration:\\n\",\n",
    "      \"  Optimizer: Adam (adaptive learning rate)\\n\",\n",
    "      \"  Loss: SparseCategoricalCrossentropy\\n\",\n",
    "      \"  Metrics: Accuracy\\n\"\n",
    "     ]\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": 7\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Quick Check: Initial Loss\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Let's see the loss before training:\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2026-01-13T13:26:54.916022100Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2026-01-13T13:26:54.873097400Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Calculate loss for first example\\n\",\n",
    "    \"loss_fn = keras.losses.SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(from_logits=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"initial_loss = loss_fn(y_train[:1], predictions).numpy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Initial loss: {initial_loss:.3f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\nFor a random guess (10 classes), expected loss ≈ -log(1/10) ≈ 2.3\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Our untrained model: {initial_loss:.3f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\n→ Close to random! Training will reduce this loss.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [\n",
    "    {\n",
    "     \"name\": \"stdout\",\n",
    "     \"output_type\": \"stream\",\n",
    "     \"text\": [\n",
    "      \"Initial loss: 2.464\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\n\",\n",
    "      \"For a random guess (10 classes), expected loss ≈ -log(1/10) ≈ 2.3\\n\",\n",
    "      \"Our untrained model: 2.464\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\n\",\n",
    "      \"→ Close to random! Training will reduce this loss.\\n\"\n",
    "     ]\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": 8\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Part 5: Training the Model\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Training process:**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Show the network a batch of examples\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Network makes predictions\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Calculate loss (how wrong the predictions were)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Adjust weights to reduce loss\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. Repeat!\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Key Terms\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Epoch:** One complete pass through ALL training data\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- 1 epoch = network sees all 60,000 images once\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Batch:** Small group of examples processed together\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Default batch size = 32\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- 60,000 examples ÷ 32 = 1,875 batches per epoch\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Step:** Processing one batch\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- 1 epoch = 1,875 steps (for MNIST)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Let's train for 5 epochs:\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2026-01-13T13:27:05.787672900Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2026-01-13T13:26:54.919537700Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Train the model\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Training started...\\\\n\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"history = model.fit(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    x_train,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    y_train,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    epochs=5,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    verbose=1  # Show progress\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\n✓ Training complete!\\\")\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [\n",
    "    {\n",
    "     \"name\": \"stdout\",\n",
    "     \"output_type\": \"stream\",\n",
    "     \"text\": [\n",
    "      \"Training started...\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\n\",\n",
    "      \"Epoch 1/5\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\u001B[1m1875/1875\\u001B[0m \\u001B[32m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\\u001B[0m\\u001B[37m\\u001B[0m \\u001B[1m3s\\u001B[0m 1ms/step - accuracy: 0.9252 - loss: 0.2608\\n\",\n",
    "      \"Epoch 2/5\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\u001B[1m1875/1875\\u001B[0m \\u001B[32m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\\u001B[0m\\u001B[37m\\u001B[0m \\u001B[1m2s\\u001B[0m 1ms/step - accuracy: 0.9665 - loss: 0.1124\\n\",\n",
    "      \"Epoch 3/5\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\u001B[1m1875/1875\\u001B[0m \\u001B[32m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\\u001B[0m\\u001B[37m\\u001B[0m \\u001B[1m2s\\u001B[0m 1ms/step - accuracy: 0.9775 - loss: 0.0762\\n\",\n",
    "      \"Epoch 4/5\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\u001B[1m1875/1875\\u001B[0m \\u001B[32m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\\u001B[0m\\u001B[37m\\u001B[0m \\u001B[1m2s\\u001B[0m 1ms/step - accuracy: 0.9823 - loss: 0.0579\\n\",\n",
    "      \"Epoch 5/5\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\u001B[1m1875/1875\\u001B[0m \\u001B[32m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\\u001B[0m\\u001B[37m\\u001B[0m \\u001B[1m2s\\u001B[0m 1ms/step - accuracy: 0.9858 - loss: 0.0457\\n\",\n",
    "      \"\\n\",\n",
    "      \"✓ Training complete!\\n\"\n",
    "     ]\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": 9\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Understanding the Training Output\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Each line shows:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Epoch X/5**: Which epoch we're on\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **1875/1875**: Progress through batches\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **loss**: How wrong predictions are (lower is better)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **accuracy**: % of correct predictions (higher is better)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **time**: How long it took\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**What to look for:**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- ✓ Loss should **decrease** over epochs\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- ✓ Accuracy should **increase** over epochs\\n\",\n",
