    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Summary\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Congratulations! You've learned:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"✓ What neural networks are and how they work  \\n\",\n",
    "    \"✓ Key components: layers, activation functions, loss  \\n\",\n",
    "    \"✓ How to build a neural network with Keras  \\n\",\n",
    "    \"✓ How to train and evaluate models  \\n\",\n",
    "    \"✓ How to make predictions with trained models  \\n\",\n",
    "    \"✓ How to apply neural networks to image classification  \\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Key Takeaways:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Neural networks learn from examples** - Show patterns, network finds them\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Architecture matters** - More layers/neurons = more capacity to learn\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Training is iterative** - Network improves with each epoch\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Test on unseen data** - True measure of generalization\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Preprocessing is important** - Normalize inputs (0-1 range)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### What's Next?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Improve your models:**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Try different architectures (more layers, more neurons)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Add dropout to prevent overfitting\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Use data augmentation for more training examples\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Try different optimizers (SGD, RMSprop)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Advanced topics:**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs)** - Better for images\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs)** - For sequences (text, time series)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Transfer Learning** - Use pre-trained models\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Custom Training Loops** - More control over training\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Additional Resources:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- [TensorFlow Tutorials](https://www.tensorflow.org/tutorials)\\n\",\n",
